Manx: Eshyn (lesh nearey): “Mys Ealish, t-tou jeeaghyn millish dy-liooar ry-hoi paagey.”
English: He (rather backward) : “Miss Alice, y-you look sweet enough to kiss.”

Manx: Ish: “Wahll, ta mee boggoil dy hoiggal nagh vel eh yn foill aym’s.”
English: She: “Well, I’m glad to know it isn’t my fault.”
